    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="416"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 PW (Peace)/8–2947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Political Adviser in Korea</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jacobs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-11T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 11, 1947—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191. Inf <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CinCFE</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_urtel1"
                        >Urtel</gloss> 306, Aug 29. Inform Kimm Kiusic message being transmitted
                    Pres Truman and Dept giving consideration means by which Korean interests
                    connection Japanese peace settlement can best be given expression. Not clear
                    from <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> whether intended message also to be
                    sent to Dept to Prime Minister Attlee Generalissimo CKS. Dept has taken no
                    action this matter but raises question whether messages might not be transmitted
                    by Legislature or by <gloss target="#t_USAFIK1">USAFIK</gloss> acting for
                    Legislature through Chinese and British Consuls Seoul. Your comment
                        requested.<note n="47" xml:id="d416fn47">Telegram 344, September 13, from
                        Seoul, stated that the messages had already been transmitted through the
                        Consuls and that this procedure would be followed in future cases (740.0011
                        PW (Peace)/9–1347).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
